    <section id="id12275422">
      <title>PRIMARY, SECONDARY AND TERTIARY INDUSTRIES</title>
      <list id="id14172266" list-type="enumerated" number-style="arabic">
        <item>What is primary industry?</item>
      </list>
      <para id="id10313883">These are industries that have to do with the exploitation of raw materials found in nature.</para>
      <list id="id16232312" list-type="enumerated" number-style="arabic">
        <item>What is secondary industry?</item>
      </list>
      <para id="id6776461">This involves factories that manufacture goods, i.e. industries that are involved with the conversion of raw materials into goods.</para>
      <list id="id10847101" list-type="enumerated" number-style="arabic">
        <item>What is tertiary industry?</item>
      </list>
      <para id="id11829668">These are the businesses that render the services to supply the products to the consumer or transport the products to the consumer (marketing and distribution).</para>
    </section>
