      <para id="id6870732">[LO 2.1] </para>
      <para id="id10517913">Because there are three types of industry, it is possible for us to say that a product goes through three stages of production. All products undergo these three stages of production, which are  </para>
      <para id="id11126226">This is called the <emphasis effect="bold">PRODUCTION CHAIN</emphasis>. The price increases at each link in the chain. When one of your parents therefore buys a can of preserved peaches, she or he is paying for the work of the farmer, the manufacturer, the transporter, the wholesaler and the shop owner.</para>
    </section>
